# Environment variables for JKE Tree & Crane
#
# Copy this file to `.env.local` for local development and fill in real
# values there — `.env.local` is gitignored and must never be committed.
# On your hosting platform (Vercel, etc.), add these as project environment
# variables through its dashboard, not by committing a real .env file.
#
# NOTHING in this file is required for the site to build or run today. Every
# variable below is FUTURE-ONLY, documented ahead of time so whoever wires up
# the corresponding integration knows exactly what to add and where. See
# DEPLOYMENT.md for the full explanation of each integration.
#
# Rule of thumb: only prefix a variable with NEXT_PUBLIC_ if it is safe for
# every site visitor to see in their browser (e.g. an analytics ID). Never
# prefix a real secret (API key, client secret, access token) with
# NEXT_PUBLIC_ — those must stay server-only.

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Jobber integration (FUTURE — required once the request form is connected
# to a real backend; see DEPLOYMENT.md "Jobber Integration Handoff")
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Jobber's public API is OAuth2-based. The exact variable names below are a
# reasonable starting point, not a guarantee — confirm against Jobber's
# current developer docs when this is actually implemented, and adjust to
# match whatever auth flow is used (direct API integration vs. a middleman
# like Zapier/Make, which would need a webhook URL instead of these).
# JOBBER_CLIENT_ID=
# JOBBER_CLIENT_SECRET=
# JOBBER_REFRESH_TOKEN=

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Analytics (FUTURE — optional, add only what the business owner wants live)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Google Analytics 4 measurement ID (format: G-XXXXXXXXXX). Public by design
# — GA's tracking snippet runs in the browser — so NEXT_PUBLIC_ is correct
# here, unlike the Jobber credentials above.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_GA_MEASUREMENT_ID=

# Microsoft Clarity project ID, if the business wants session-replay/heatmap
# tracking in addition to (or instead of) GA4. Also public by design.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_CLARITY_PROJECT_ID=

# Google Search Console site-verification token, only needed if verifying
# ownership via HTML meta tag (DNS or file-upload verification don't need an
# env var at all). Not a secret — safe to expose.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_SITE_VERIFICATION=

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Alternate/supplementary lead delivery (FUTURE — optional, only relevant if
# the business wants an email copy of every request in addition to Jobber)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# RESEND_API_KEY=
# FORM_NOTIFICATION_EMAIL=
